Kirk

Thanks for your reply.  How come everyone agrees? I can tell you they
don't - they have more sense than to entertain anything so crass.  My
figures show that 20 dB less power is extracted when the ferrite is
removed.  You seem to be slipping into the role of the mad hatter now
(I'm not planning to waste much time on this).

I know you have no experience with or knowledge of radio, but try
taking a transistor radio, take the ferrite rod antenna out and
replacing it with a coil of the same dimensions.  Everyone (bar one)
knows what the result will be.

Alan G3NOQ
